Class Inventory

  • java.lang.Object
    • library.inventory.Inventory
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Book, Movie

    public class Inventory
extends java.lang.Object
    The base class (parent class / super class) for all types of inventory in the Library.
    Since:
    2021.03.23
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Caden Cruise

      The inventory location.
      protected java.lang.String type

      protected double value
      The inventory's value in dollars.

        public Inventory()
        Default constructor will automatically runs when an object is created using the new keyword, and no arguments are passed to the constructor. The Java compiler will create an empty default constructor if the programmer doesn't write one. Typically the default constructor is used to handle housekeeping items when a object is first created.
